content.content:
{
  "id": "ir-mo36doz8-740ac81b",
  "rigId": "rig-mo35s0he-bf3bbb31",
  "engineId": "decision-review",
  "status": "pending",
  "message": "Planning review for: Spider Dispatch Gating via `spider.follows` (codex: nexus)\n\nIn-scope items: Link-substrate field and type rename sweep: type→label, semanticMeaning→kind, MeaningDoc→KindDoc, MeaningEntry→KindEntry, listMeanings()→listKinds(), linkMeanings→linkKinds (kit field and consumes)., Plugin-namespaced id separator sweep from ':' to '.' for qualified identifiers (link kinds, roles, event patterns, rig templates). Permissions stay on ':' (distinct grammar)., CLI tool surface update: writ-link --kind flag and rename writ-link-meanings → writ-link-kinds (tool name, HTTP route, instructions text, docstrings)., Oculus writ-page adds a kind dropdown to the inline add-link form, populated from listKinds(); label stays as free-text with existing datalist autocomplete., Per-plugin status convention on writs: top-level status slot keyed by pluginId (K8s-style), last-writer-wins per key, persists across terminal states, plugin-owned shape (unknown/untyped for v1)., Spider registers the spider.follows link kind via supportKit.linkKinds with a human-readable description; Clerk consumes it through the existing kit substrate., Spider dispatch gating: in trySpawn(), consult each candidate writ's spider.follows dependencies and conjunctively require all targets to be in a terminal state before spawning a rig., Stuck cascade on failed blocker: when any spider.follows target is in a failed terminal state, transition the dependent writ from open to stuck with a human-readable resolution and status.spider.stuckCause='failed-blocker'., Cycle detection: when evaluating a candidate writ, walk the spider.follows graph and if a cycle is detected, mark all cycle participants stuck with status.spider.stuckCause='cycle' and a human-readable resolution., Auto-unstick on blocker recovery: each poll, Spider scans stuck writs whose status.spider.stuckCause is set, re-evaluates their spider.follows graph, and transitions stuck→open (clearing the cause) when the stuck condition no longer holds., Documentation updates: Spider README/arch-doc for gating and status.spider slot; Clerk README/arch-doc for label/kind/listKinds/KindDoc; any prose docs referencing colon-form link-kind ids.",
  "questions": {
    "D1": {
      "type": "choice",
      "label": "How is the name collision between the existing WritDoc.status (lifecycle phase, WritStatus) and the new per-plugin status slot (Record<PluginId, unknown>) resolved on writs?",
      "details": "WritDoc today has a top-level field named `status` of type WritStatus ('new'|'open'|'stuck'|'completed'|'failed'|'cancelled'). The brief and click c-mo33duvq describe the new per-plugin slot as being literally named `status`, referenced as `status.spider.stuckCause`. Both names cannot coexist as-is. The concluded clicks specify last-writer-wins per plugin key, implicit default of {}, and CDC emission through the normal mutation path — they assume a shape, but they don't name the field.\n\nRecommendation rationale: Minimal blast radius, preserves the one-shot 'in-place rename' assumption the brief endorses elsewhere, and keeps WritFilters/CDC/transition machinery untouched. The name variance from the brief's literal wording is small enough to resolve in the spec; the shape (Record<PluginId, unknown>) is preserved.",
      "options": {
        "a-rename-new-slot": "Pick a different name for the new slot (e.g. `pluginStatus`, `observers`, `extensions`). Leave WritDoc.status untouched as the lifecycle phase. Example becomes `pluginStatus.spider.stuckCause`. Minimal blast radius — only new code touches the new field.",
        "b-rename-existing-phase": "Rename the existing WritDoc.status to WritDoc.phase (or similar). Free up `status` for the new slot shape. Large blast radius: every clerk/spider/page/test read of `writ.status === 'open'` updates to `writ.phase`. Matches brief/click literal naming.",
        "c-k8s-restructure": "Restructure WritDoc.status to be the Record<PluginId, unknown> itself, with the lifecycle phase promoted into `status.phase` (K8s-style). `writ.status.phase === 'open'`, `writ.status.spider.stuckCause === '...'`. Deepest blast radius but the most faithful K8s analogy; adds nested-field filtering concerns to WritFilters.",
        "d-scope-by-convention": "Keep WritDoc.status as WritStatus, but establish that the *convention* (the new K8s-style slot) is written as a sibling field named something else on a per-apparatus basis (e.g. the spider slot is WritDoc.spiderStatus). Loses the uniform Record<PluginId, unknown> shape the brief describes but avoids any rename."
      },
      "allowCustom": true
    },
    "scope:S1": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "label": "Link-substrate field and type rename sweep: type→label, semanticMeaning→kind, MeaningDoc→KindDoc, MeaningEntry→KindEntry, listMeanings()→listKinds(), linkMeanings→linkKinds (kit field and consumes).",
      "details": "Brief names these as a coordinated rename to match the vocabulary landing in this commission (kind = load-bearing identity, label = casual text)."
    },
    "scope:S2": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "label": "Plugin-namespaced id separator sweep from ':' to '.' for qualified identifiers (link kinds, roles, event patterns, rig templates). Permissions stay on ':' (distinct grammar).",
      "details": "Brief calls out the separator unification so qualified ids read consistently across the guild; click c-mo34644p prescribes the replacement."
    },
    "scope:S3": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "label": "CLI tool surface update: writ-link --kind flag and rename writ-link-meanings → writ-link-kinds (tool name, HTTP route, instructions text, docstrings).",
      "details": "The rename propagates to operator-visible command and flag names; the tool server exposes the tool by its route, so the shift is user-facing."
    },
    "scope:S4": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "label": "Oculus writ-page adds a kind dropdown to the inline add-link form, populated from listKinds(); label stays as free-text with existing datalist autocomplete.",
      "details": "The brief explicitly adds a kind control on the writ page so link kinds can be set from the UI rather than CLI-only."
    },
    "scope:S5": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "label": "Per-plugin status convention on writs: top-level status slot keyed by pluginId (K8s-style), last-writer-wins per key, persists across terminal states, plugin-owned shape (unknown/untyped for v1).",
      "details": "Brief establishes this as a guild-wide convention and lands the first slot (spider) in this commission; concluded clicks (c-mo33dxf5, c-mo33duvq, c-mo33dyln, c-mo33dz7m, c-mo33e065, c-mo33e1vs) pre-decide its semantics."
    },
    "scope:S6": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "label": "Spider registers the spider.follows link kind via supportKit.linkKinds with a human-readable description; Clerk consumes it through the existing kit substrate.",
      "details": "First real consumer of link kinds; without registration the ingest/validation pipeline rejects writes."
    },
    "scope:S7": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "label": "Spider dispatch gating: in trySpawn(), consult each candidate writ's spider.follows dependencies and conjunctively require all targets to be in a terminal state before spawning a rig.",
      "details": "The core feature — without this, spider.follows carries no behavior."
    },
    "scope:S8": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "label": "Stuck cascade on failed blocker: when any spider.follows target is in a failed terminal state, transition the dependent writ from open to stuck with a human-readable resolution and status.spider.stuckCause='failed-blocker'.",
      "details": "Brief prescribes cascade behavior and structured provenance so recovery flows can distinguish spider-authored stucks from engine-authored ones."
    },
    "scope:S9": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "label": "Cycle detection: when evaluating a candidate writ, walk the spider.follows graph and if a cycle is detected, mark all cycle participants stuck with status.spider.stuckCause='cycle' and a human-readable resolution.",
      "details": "Brief names cycles as a distinct failure mode with its own stuckCause value."
    },
    "scope:S10": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "label": "Auto-unstick on blocker recovery: each poll, Spider scans stuck writs whose status.spider.stuckCause is set, re-evaluates their spider.follows graph, and transitions stuck→open (clearing the cause) when the stuck condition no longer holds.",
      "details": "Brief prescribes auto-recovery so that operator-driven or out-of-band unblocking flows don't require manual unstick."
    },
    "scope:S11": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "label": "Documentation updates: Spider README/arch-doc for gating and status.spider slot; Clerk README/arch-doc for label/kind/listKinds/KindDoc; any prose docs referencing colon-form link-kind ids.",
      "details": "Brief lists prose doc surfaces as in-scope for the sweep, and the new Spider semantics need narrative coverage."
    }
  },
  "answers": {
    "D1": {
      "selected": "a-rename-new-slot"
    },
    "scope:S1": true,
    "scope:S2": true,
    "scope:S3": true,
    "scope:S4": true,
    "scope:S5": true,
    "scope:S6": true,
    "scope:S7": true,
    "scope:S8": true,
    "scope:S9": true,
    "scope:S10": true,
    "scope:S11": true
  },
  "createdAt": "2026-04-17T17:21:41.300Z",
  "updatedAt": "2026-04-17T17:21:41.300Z"
}

