  "description": "Rename the writ lifecycle field from `status` to `phase` across the entire guild — WritStatus → WritPhase type alias, WritDoc.status → WritDoc.phase, WritFilters.status → WritFilters.phase, ClerkApi.transition() parameter, all Clerk runtime references (ALLOWED_FROM, TERMINAL_STATUSES, buildWhereClause, post, edit, transition, CDC watcher, book indexes), all Clerk tool schemas and response shapes (writ-list, writ-show), all Clerk page filter attributes and URL params, and all Spider references (dispatch-filter query, CDC watchers on writs and rigs books, writ-status block type field reads). Value strings (`'new' | 'open' | 'stuck' | 'completed' | 'failed' | 'cancelled'`) are unchanged."
}
{
  "id": "S2",
  "description": "Introduce the observation slot `WritDoc.status?: Record<string, unknown>` — plugin-owned sub-slots keyed by plugin id. The slot survives terminal phase transitions, changes emit CDC events like any field change, ownership is by convention only (no code guards), and the `transition()` managed-field strip list must no longer strip `status` (since `status` is now user-writable)."
}
{
  "id": "S3",
  "description": "Document the spec/status convention guild-wide — add a dedicated section to `packages/plugins/clerk/README.md` and `docs/architecture/apparatus/clerk.md` explaining the K8s-style split (`phase` owned by Clerk, `status` observation slot owned by convention), sub-slot write semantics, CDC behavior, persistence across terminal states, concurrent-write guidance, and a worked example showing how a future consumer (Spider's `status.spider.stuckCause`) would plug in."
}
{
  "id": "S4",
  "description": "Migrate persisted writ rows at Clerk startup — a one-shot idempotent pass that reads every row in the `writs` book, moves the old `status` lifecycle value into `phase` (collapsing legacy `ready`/`active`/`waiting` → `open` as the existing legacyStatuses migration does today), and rewrites the row so the old `status` field is gone (via `put()`, since Stacks `patch()` cannot remove fields). Runs inside `start()` before the CDC registry seals, subsuming the existing legacyStatuses migration."
}

